Reasoning: The paper deals with curve parameterization in computer vision applications, specifically for fitting closed contours to a set of points. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of ellipses for curve fitting, which is a common technique in computer graphics (cs.GR). The paper also introduces a new algorithm for curve fitting that is robust to outliers, which suggests that it may be relevant to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper demonstrates the utility of the algorithm for image segmentation, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
